                <head>77. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In its December 7 Progress Report on <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5506
                        (<ref target="#d7">Document 7</ref>), the <gloss target="#t_OCB1"
                        >OCB</gloss> stated:</p>
                <p>“The Board recommends that the Council review the policy set forth in <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5506. This is desirable in view of the fact
                    that the Council is currently reviewing <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5501
                    and the need for relating the policies set forth in <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5506 and <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5429/5 to the new
                    policy. The Board noted that developments since the approval of <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5506 with respect to such matters as East-West
                    trade, Soviet economic penetration, and the economic burden of local military
                    establishments, make such a policy review desirable.” (Department of State,
                        S/S–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 63 D 351, <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5506 Series)</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5501, “Basic National Security Policy”,
                    January 6, 1955, is scheduled for publicaition in <ref target="frus1955-57v19"
                        >volume XIX</ref>.</p>
                <p>At its meeting on January 18, 1956, the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    discussed this progress report and requested the Council on Foreign Economic
                    Policy, “after Council and Presidential action on the forthcoming revision of
                    Basic National Security Policy (<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5501), to
                    review <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5506 in the light of such basic
                    policy and report its findings back to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>.”
                        (<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 1506; Department of State,
                        S/S–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> (Miscellaneous) Files: Lot 66 D 95,
                    Records of Action by the National Security Council)</p>
